        "parts": [
          {
            "text": "For teen acne treatment options in Katy, Texas, consider the following:\n\n**Treatment Options:**\n\n*   **Topical and Oral Medications:** Prescription topical or oral antibiotics can target and kill bacteria, especially in cases of cystic acne. Benzoyl peroxide products help unclog pores, addressing blackheads and whiteheads. Tretinoin medications are also used to clear pores, often recommended for severe acne.\n*   **Laser Therapy:** Laser therapy can be used to kill bacteria causing skin infections.  Acne laser therapy uses pulsed light to cleanse pores, purify the skin, and replenish it.  BBL \"Forever Clear Acne Treatments\" use pulsed light to control sebum, remove blackheads and debris, and kill acne-causing bacteria.\n*   **Extraction Treatment:**  This involves the removal of blackheads and whiteheads.\n*   **Acne Scarring Treatment:** Options include topical therapies, chemical peels, laser resurfacing, and microneedling.\n*   **Photodynamic Therapy:**  This therapy uses intense pulsed light and blue LED light to destroy acne-causing bacteria and shrink oil-producing glands.\n\n**Clinics and Specialists in Katy, TX:**\n\n*   **4Ever Young Anti-aging Clinic and Medical Spa:** Offers specialized acne treatments targeting the root cause and eliminating acne-damaged cells. They provide personalized treatment plans and prescription medications.\n    *   **Phone:** (346) 988-2190\n*   **AcneFix:**  Offers acne treatment programs suitable for both teens and adults, customizing treatment plans based on age, skin type, and specific needs.\n*   **Cinco Ranch Dermatology:** Provides expert acne treatment for all ages, with personalized care plans ranging from basic skin regimens to advanced therapies like Accutane.\n*   **Dermatology Associates of Katy, PLLC:** Dr. Uyen Ngoc Mui offers various acne treatment options, including prescription medications, laser therapy, and extraction treatments.\n*   **About Face & Body:** Offers acne laser therapy treatments.\n\n**General Tips to Prevent Acne:**\n\n*   Exercise regularly.\n*   Practice stress reduction techniques.\n*   Limit greasy foods, soda, and dairy.\n*   Drink at least 8 glasses of water daily.\n*   Clean your cell phone regularly.\n*   Use non-comedogenic makeup.\n*   Change your pillowcase weekly.\n*   Avoid touching your face.\n\nIt's important to consult with a dermatologist or acne specialist to determine the most appropriate treatment plan for your specific needs. They can assess your skin, discuss your goals, and recommend the best course of action.\n"
          }
        ],
